data.chText: 值得注意的；显著的；重要的
data.enText: deserving to be noticed or to receive attention; important

data.chText: 显著的成功 / 成就；明显的事例
他的双眼是他最明显的特征。
data.enText: His eyes are his most notable feature .

data.chText: 这座小镇因其古老的港口而出名。
data.enText: The town is notable for its ancient harbour.

data.chText: 人人都给了些东西，只有几个人例外，很是显眼。
data.enText: With a few notable exceptions , everyone gave something.

data.chText: 经常露面的地方名流都在那里。
data.enText: All the usual local notables were there.

simple_means.memory_skill: not 标记 + able …的 → 加了标记的 → 值得注意的

tr: a celebrity who is an inspiration to others
example: he was host to a large gathering of luminaries
a noteworthy advance in cancer research

value.def: Someone or something that is notable is important or interesting.

example.ex: The proposed new structure is notable not only for its height, but for its shape...
example.tran: 拟建的新建筑令人瞩目，不仅是因其高度，也因其外形。

example.ex: Mo did not want to be ruled by anyone and it is notable that she never allowed the men in her life to eclipse her...
example.tran: 莫不想受任何人支配，而且很明显她从不容许自己生活里的男性光芒盖过自己。

example.ex: With a few notable exceptions, doctors are a pretty sensible lot.
example.tran: 除了一些有趣的例外，医生都是些讲求实际的家伙。

value.tran: 值得注意的;显著的;有趣的

example.ex: Elected by local notables for nine years Senators lack the democratic legitimacy of members of the National Assembly...
example.tran: 由当地名流选出、任职9年的参议员缺少国民议会议员的民主合法性。

example.ex: The notables include five Senators, two Supreme Court judges and three State Governors.
example.tran: 显要人物包括五名参议员、两名最高法院法官和三名州长。

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to know, mark 知道；标记
rootsaffixes.title: not

partsOfSpeech.dec: an 加强 + not 知道；标记 + ate 做 → 做标记 → 注解
an 加强 + not 知道；标记 + ation 行为，过程，状态，结果 → 注解
de 加强 + not 知道；标记 + e → 做标记 → 指示
not 知道；标记 + able …的 → 加了标记的 → 值得注意的
not 知道；标记 + ice 表行为 → 使知道；做标记引起注意 → 注意；通知
not 知道；标记 + ify 使… → 使…知道 → 通知
not 知道；标记 + ion 表名词 → 为让人知道而表达的自己的见解和观点 → 见解；观念
not 知道；标记 + or 表人 + ious 多…的 →〔因做坏事〕让很多人知道 → 恶名昭彰的
